# TECH INDIA-Volunteer Registration Web App
The Volunteer Registration Web App is a simple Flask-based web application that allows volunteers to 
register for a classroom assistance program. Volunteers can provide their name, location, spoken languages, 
and availability using the web form, and their registration details will be stored and displayed on the website.

### Table of Contents
#### Features
#### Getting Started
##### Prerequisites
##### Installation
#### Usage
#### Contributing
#### License

## Features
Volunteer Registration: Volunteers can fill out a form with their name, location, spoken languages, and 
availability to register for the classroom assistance program.
Volunteer List: A list of registered volunteers is displayed on the website, showing their basic details.

## Getting Started
### Prerequisites
Python (version 3.6 or higher)
Flask (version 1.1.2 or higher)

### Installation
Clone the repository to your local machine:git clone https://github.com/rahimunshaik/volunteer-registration-app.git
Navigate to the project directory:cd volunteer-registration-app
Install the required Python packages using pip:
pip install -r requirements.txt

## Usage

Run the Flask app:
### python app.py
Open your web browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5000/ to access the Volunteer Registration page.
Fill out the registration form with your details and click the "Register" button.
An alert message will be displayed confirming that you have successfully registered as a volunteer.
To view the list of registered volunteers, go to http://127.0.0.1:5000/volunteers.

